rick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Wotton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Wooten  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Wooten","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called with Old English <i>wid(u)</i>, <i>wudu</i> ‘wood’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, such as Wootton in Northamptonshire or Oxfordshire, Wootton Bassett in Wiltshire, Wotton in Surrey, and Wotton under Edge in Gloucestershire."]}]},{"name":"Johannes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Johannes Harwell De Wotton was born in 1374, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Harewell, was 27 and his mother, Margaret Beaupine, was 21. He married Mrs Johannes Harwell De Wotton. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"1374–":"1374–Surnud","1373–1435":"1373–1435","1374–Male":"1374–Surnud","1387–1416":"1387–1416","1395–1499":"1395–1499","1376–Female":"1376–Surnud","1395–1491":"1395–1491","1401–1436":"1401–1436","1403–Female":